HEADWORD: Breakwater
<hw>Break"wa`ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any structure
or contrivance, as a mole, or a wall at the mouth of a harbor, to break
the force of waves, and afford protection from their violence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

